---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";
import { ArrowLeft, ArrowRight } from "@lucide/astro";
---

<CaseStudyLayout
    title="Case Study: Architecting an Engagement Engine | Kunal Katre"
>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div
        slot="hero"
        class="hero-section not-prose min-h-[var(--hero-height-mobile)] md:min-h-[var(--hero-height-tablet)] lg:min-h-[var(--hero-height-desktop)] mb-12 animate-fade-in w-full"
    >
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 items-center">
            <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
                <a
                    href="/#work"
                    class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm gap-2 pl-0 hover:bg-transparent hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-300"
                >
                    <ArrowLeft />
                    Back to Work
                </a>

                <div
                    class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm font-medium text-base-content/70"
                >
                    <span>Project for</span>
                    <img
                        src="/assets/eka-logo.svg"
                        alt="Eka Care logo"
                        class="h-6 w-auto"
                    />
                </div>

                <h1
                    class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold leading-tight"
                >
                    Architecting an Engagement Engine
                </h1>

                <p
                    class="text-xl text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
                >
                    I transformed a failing feature with 38% user drop-off into
                    a core driver of engagement and retention for the Eka.Care
                    platform.
                </p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 pt-4">
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary">+21%</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Conversion Lift
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary">2x</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Week 4 Retention
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent">
                            4 Months
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Oct â€“ Jan 2023
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="flex-1 w-full max-w-sm lg:max-w-full flex justify-center"
            >
                <div
                    class="phone-mockup mockup-phone w-60 h-[480px] sm:w-72 sm:h-[568px] md:w-80 md:h-[640px] border-primary"
                >
                    <div class="camera"></div>
                    <div class="display">
                        <div
                            class="bg-black overflow-hidden relative phone-mockup w-60 h-[480px] sm:w-72 sm:h-[568px] md:w-80 md:h-[640px]"
                        >
                            <!-- Video Content -->
                            <video
                                src="/src/assets/hr/instruction video-1.mp4"
                                autoplay
                                loop
                                muted
                                playsinline
                                poster="/src/assets/hr/result-final-dashboard.png"
                                class="w-full h-full object-cover"></video>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <section id="setup">
            <h2>1. The Setup: A Leaky Funnel & a Crisis of Trust</h2>
            <p>
                In late 2022, the Heart Rate Monitor (BPM) was a strategic bet
                on organic growth and user engagement. The business objective
                was two-fold: create a "wow" moment for <strong
                    >first-time users</strong
                > to drive acquisition, and build a valuable tool that <strong
                    >repeat users</strong
                > would integrate into their health routines.
            </p>
            <p>
                However, analytics painted a grim picture. The feature was
                underperforming dramatically. Our primary business metrics were
                failing:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>First-Time User Conversion:</strong> A catastrophic ~38%
                    of users were dropping off before successfully completing their
                    first measurement.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Long-Term Retention:</strong> Churn analysis showed that
                    even users who were successful once rarely came back. The feature
                    wasn't "sticking."
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <section id="research">
            <h2>2. Discovery: Uncovering the 'Why'</h2>
            <h3>2.1 Guerilla Research: The Insights Grid</h3>
            <p>
                The data showed *what* was happening, but not *why*. I initiated
                a quick guerilla research sprint, conducting informal usability
                tests with a diverse user group. The unfiltered feedback was raw
                and illuminating.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/hr/research.png"
                    alt="Guerilla Research in progress"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig. 1 - Conducting informal usability tests to quickly
                    gather qualitative insights.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
                <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body p-6">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            Instruction Mismatch
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            "I see the instructions, but I don't understand
                            them. The words are difficult and I don't know which
                            camera to use."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body p-6">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            The "Phone Flip" Behavior
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            "It's hard to do without looking at the back!"
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body p-6">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            Trust & Accuracy Concerns
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            "I just came from running, but my heart rate shown
                            is 58. I don't trust the reading."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>
                2.2 Analyzing the V1 Experience: The 4-Step Failure Analysis
            </h3>
            <p>
                Armed with user insights, I conducted a systematic analysis of
                the V1 experience to identify the root causes of the 38%
                drop-off. This analysis revealed a cascade of failures at each
                stage of the user journey.
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Step 1: The Instruction Barrier
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            V1 presented complex medical terminology ("Place
                            finger firmly on camera lens") without visual
                            guidance. Users couldn't distinguish between front
                            and back cameras, leading to immediate confusion and
                            abandonment.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Step 2: The Measurement Anxiety
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Users had no visual feedback during the 15-second
                            measurement. The lack of progress indicators and
                            real-time feedback created uncertainty about whether
                            the feature was working, leading to premature finger
                            movement and failed measurements.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Step 3: The Trust Deficit
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Results appeared without context or validation.
                            Users had no way to understand if the reading was
                            accurate for their situation (post-exercise,
                            resting, etc.), creating immediate skepticism about
                            the feature's reliability.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Step 4: The Dead End
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            The results screen provided no actionable insights
                            or next steps. Users got a single data point with no
                            guidance on what to do with it, eliminating any
                            reason to return and measure again.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>2.3 Synthesizing with a User Journey Map</h3>
            <p>
                I consolidated all these findings into two comprehensive
                Emotional Journey Maps that became our team's shared source of
                truth. These artifacts translated abstract data and user quotes
                into clear narratives of declining trust and broken engagement
                loops.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/hr/FTUX-journey-map.webp"
                    alt="Emotional journey map diagnosing the V1 experience"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig. 2 - First-Time User Experience journey map showing the
                    cascade of trust erosion from confusion to abandonment.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-4">
                This map diagnosed the V1 experience, revealing how small
                friction points compounded into a catastrophic 38% drop-off. The
                emotional journey showed users starting with curiosity but
                quickly descending into frustration and distrust.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/hr/RTUX-journey-map.webp"
                    alt="V1 Returning User Experience journey map"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig. 3 - Returning User Experience journey map revealing a
                    broken loop with no long-term value.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-4">
                The returning user map was equally revealing. Even users who
                succeeded once found no reason to return, creating a engagement
                dead-end that directly contradicted our business goals of
                building habitual usage.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <section id="goals">
            <h2>3. Defining the Design Goals</h2>
            <p>
                With a deep, evidence-backed understanding of the problem, I
                established three clear, measurable design goals that would
                guide our entire redesign effort:
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-base-content/10 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            1
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            First-Try Success
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80">
                            Overhaul the onboarding and measurement experience
                            to be foolproof, intuitive, and anxiety-free for all
                            users.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-base-content/10 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            2
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            Unshakeable Trust
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80">
                            Provide transparent, real-time feedback and
                            proactively educate users to eliminate confusion and
                            build confidence in the result.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-base-content/10 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            3
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            Create a Habit Loop
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80">
                            Transform the results screen from a dead end into an
                            actionable, insightful launchpad that provides clear
                            value and encourages repeat usage.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <section id="design">
            <h2>4. Iteration & Design</h2>
            <p>
                To tackle our goals, I mapped specific design interventions to
                each stage of the user journey. This strategic diagram guided
                our design exploration.
            </p>

            <!-- Onboarding -->
            <h3>
                4.1 Solving for 'First-Try' Success: Detailed Onboarding
                Interventions
            </h3>
            <p>
                Fixing the 38% drop-off required a multi-point attack on the
                onboarding journey. I broke the problem down into distinct
                intervention points and designed comprehensive solutions for
                each.
            </p>

            <div
                class="card bg-base-200/30 border border-base-300 my-8 overflow-hidden"
            >
                <figure
                    class="w-full aspect-video bg-base-300 flex items-center justify-center"
                >
                    <!-- Placeholder or use video from assets if available otherwise use image -->
                    <video
                        src="/src/assets/hr/instruction video-1.mp4"
                        controls
                        class="w-full h-full object-contain"></video>
                </figure>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h4 class="card-title">The "Wow" Moment Video</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm">
                        We combined technical clarity with human warmth. The
                        final video is fast-paced, human-centric, and crucially
                        includes a "5M+ Readings Recorded" social proof element
                        to instantly build trust.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Pre-Measurement Preparation</h3>
            <p>
                Understanding that users needed preparation time, I designed a
                pre-measurement screen that addressed the "phone flip" behavior
                and set proper expectations.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/pre-measure-concept-1.webp"
                        alt="Pre-measurement concept showing phone positioning guide"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>Concept: Visual positioning guide</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/pre-measure-final.webp"
                        alt="Final pre-measurement screen with clear instructions"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>
                        Final: Clear, actionable preparation steps
                    </figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>

            <h3>Designing a Proactive Safety Net</h3>
            <p>
                My analysis showed that V1 handled errors passivelyâ€”it only told
                the user *after* they had already failed. I explored a more
                proactive approach to prevent failure before it happens.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/error-handling-passive.webp"
                        alt="Passive error handling"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>Before: Passive Handling</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/error-handling-active.webp"
                        alt="Active error handling"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>After: Active real-time feedback</figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>

            <h3>
                4.2 Building Trust During Measurement: Visual Feedback and
                Sensory Rationale
            </h3>
            <p>
                During the 15-second measurement window, users need constant
                reassurance that the feature is working correctly. I designed a
                multi-sensory feedback system that addressed both visual and
                psychological needs.
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Real-Time Visual Indicators
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            A pulsing circle synchronized with heartbeat
                            detection provides immediate visual feedback. The
                            color changes from blue (detecting) to green
                            (detected) to red (analyzing), giving users a clear
                            understanding of what's happening at each stage.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Progressive Measurement Guidance
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Textual guidance appears at each stage: "Place
                            finger on camera" â†’ "Perfect! Keep steady" â†’
                            "Analyzing...". This eliminates uncertainty and
                            prevents premature finger movement that causes
                            measurement failures.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Contextual Accuracy Education
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Before showing results, we explain factors affecting
                            accuracy: "For best results, measure after resting
                            for 5 minutes." This manages expectations and builds
                            trust in the reading's validity.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/measuring-1.png"
                        alt="Initial measurement screen with finger placement guide"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>Step 1: Finger Placement</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/measuring-2.png"
                        alt="Measurement in progress with visual feedback"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>Step 2: Detection in Progress</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src="/src/assets/hr/measuring-final.png"
                        alt="Final measurement screen with analysis complete"
                        class="rounded-xl border border-base-300"
                    />
                    <figcaption>Step 3: Analysis Complete</figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>

            <h3>
                4.3 Designing an Actionable Result: Contextual Results, Habit
                Loop, and Engagement Engine
            </h3>
            <p>
                Fixing the measurement was half the battle. To drive retention,
                I redesigned the result screen to transform it from a dead-end
                data point into a rich, contextual health dashboard that creates
                a habit loop.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/hr/result-final.png"
                    alt="Full scrollable view of the final heart rate result screen dashboard"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    The Final Result: A Unified Health Dashboard with actionable
                    insights.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Contextual Results with Ranges
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Results are presented with contextual ranges: "Your
                            resting heart rate is 62 bpm - Excellent for your
                            age group!" This transforms a raw number into
                            meaningful health insight and builds confidence in
                            the measurement's accuracy.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            The Habit Loop Engine
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            I designed a complete habit loop: Measure â†’ Get
                            insights â†’ Set reminders â†’ Track trends â†’ Measure
                            again. The dashboard shows historical data, trends,
                            and personalized recommendations, creating multiple
                            reasons for users to return.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-3">
                            Proactive Engagement Triggers
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Smart notifications based on patterns: "Your resting
                            heart rate has improved by 8% this month!" or "Time
                            for your weekly heart health check-in." These
                            triggers transform passive measurement into active
                            health monitoring.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/hr/actionable-trends.png"
                    alt="Heart rate trends dashboard showing historical data and insights"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    The Engagement Engine: Transforming single measurements into
                    long-term health tracking.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 5 -->
        <section id="impact">
            <h2>5. Impact & Learnings</h2>
            <h3>Positioning Eka as a Trustworthy Health Partner</h3>
            <p>
                This initiative was more than a redesign; it was a strategic
                turnaround. By grounding our decisions in deep user research and
                data, we transformed a failing feature into a core pillar of the
                Eka.Care experience.
            </p>

            <h3>Detailed Conversion Funnel Analysis</h3>
            <p>
                The redesign delivered remarkable improvements across the entire
                user journey, with the most significant impact coming from
                addressing the critical 38% drop-off point.
            </p>

            <div
                class="bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300 rounded-xl p-6 my-8"
            >
                <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">Conversion Funnel Lift</h4>
                <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-sm font-medium"
                            >Feature Discovery</span
                        >
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <div
                                class="w-32 h-2 bg-base-300 rounded-full overflow-hidden"
                            >
                                <div class="w-full h-full bg-primary"></div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="text-sm font-bold">100%</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-sm font-medium"
                            >Start Measurement</span
                        >
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <div
                                class="w-32 h-2 bg-base-300 rounded-full overflow-hidden"
                            >
                                <div class="w-full h-full bg-primary"></div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="text-sm font-bold">100%</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-sm font-medium"
                            >Complete Measurement</span
                        >
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <div
                                class="w-32 h-2 bg-base-300 rounded-full overflow-hidden"
                            >
                                <div class="w-[62%] h-full bg-primary"></div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="text-sm font-bold">62%</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-sm font-medium">View Results</span>
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <div
                                class="w-32 h-2 bg-base-300 rounded-full overflow-hidden"
                            >
                                <div class="w-[58%] h-full bg-secondary"></div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="text-sm font-bold">58%</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-sm font-medium"
                            >Return Within 7 Days</span
                        >
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <div
                                class="w-32 h-2 bg-base-300 rounded-full overflow-hidden"
                            >
                                <div class="w-[35%] h-full bg-accent"></div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="text-sm font-bold">35%</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-primary/10 rounded-lg">
                    <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary">
                        <strong>Key Insight:</strong> The 21% conversion lift came
                        primarily from the 38% â†’ 62% improvement in first-time measurement
                        completion, proving that reducing friction at critical moments
                        drives disproportionate business value.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Retention Performance Dashboard</h3>
            <p>
                The redesigned feature created a powerful retention engine, with
                users returning consistently over time to track their heart
                health trends.
            </p>

            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="table table-compact w-full">
                    <thead>
                        <tr class="text-left">
                            <th>Time Period</th>
                            <th>Retention Rate</th>
